<img src="https://biz-file.com/c/1910/521891-625x325.jpg" alt="Image source: Gallo/Getty." width="625" height="325">Image source: Gallo/Getty.“We already covered 25% of the population. Currently, we have installed infrastructure in Bouaflé region. By cumulating the two areas, we are expecting to cover 40% of the population. We are currently working to reach 35 more sites.’According to the authorities, 95% of the Ivorian population will receive DTT by 2020. To recall, the DTT switch over deadline set by ITU for Ivory Coast is July 2020 and have cost about 22 billion FCFA.  Source: NexTVAfrica.com.